<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="82" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,435,967]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,652,678]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Remarks:</emphasis>
Molecular data suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1866" box="[643,770,652,679]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="kinbergi">
<emphasis box="[643,663,653,679]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[678,770,652,678]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">kinbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a southern Australian species (T. O’Hara, personal communication, 
<date box="[289,434,688,714]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="2019-08">August 2019</date>
) and that Indian Ocean specimens could be called 
<taxonomicName authority="(Brock, 1888)" authorityName="Brock" authorityYear="1888" baseAuthorityName="Brock" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[995,1331,688,714]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis box="[995,1166,688,714]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Ophiura indica</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Brock, J." box="[1180,1323,688,714]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" pagination="465 - 539" refId="ref13772" refString="Brock, J. (1888) Die Ophiuridenfauna des indischen Archipels. Zeitschrift fur wissenschaftliche Zoologie, 47, 465 - 539." type="journal article" year="1888">Brock, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Brock" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Ophiura indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished by its noticeably rounded primary disc plates (T. O’Hara, personal communication, 
<date box="[151,300,760,786]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" value="2019-08">August 2019</date>
), but since we did not collect this species, we cannot decide, whether reports from the study area are based on misidentifications. 
<bibRefCitation author="Mortensen, T." box="[470,671,796,823]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" pagination="55 - 112" refId="ref16691" refString="Mortensen, T. (1940) Echinoderms from the Iranian Gulf. Asteroidea, Ophiuroidea, and Echinoidea. Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran, Part 2, 55 - 112." type="book chapter" year="1940">Mortensen (1940)</bibRefCitation>
neither discussed his identification of this species nor figured it, and the drawings in 
<bibRefCitation author="Price, A. R. G." box="[328,467,832,858]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" pagination="28 - 108" refId="ref17950" refString="Price, A. R. G. (1983) Echinoderms of Saudi Arabia: Echinoderms of the Arabian Gulf Coast of Saudi Arabia. In: Wittmer, W. &amp; Buttiker, W. (Eds.), Fauna of Saudi Arabia. Karger Libri, Basel, pp. 28 - 108." type="book chapter" year="1983">Price (1983)</bibRefCitation>
are inconclusive. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E." box="[668,911,832,859]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" refId="ref14301" refString="Clark, A. M. &amp; Rowe, F. W. E. (1971) Monograph of Shallow-water Indo-west Pacific Echinoderms. Trustees of the British Museum (Natural History), London, 234 pp." type="book" year="1971">Clark &amp; Rowe (1971)</bibRefCitation>
included 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1866" box="[1020,1145,832,859]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="kinbergi">
<emphasis box="[1020,1040,833,859]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">O</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1053,1145,832,858]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">kinbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the only shallow-water species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1801" box="[270,365,868,894]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[270,365,868,894]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Ophiura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Indian Ocean, but they figured a specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[989,1056,868,894]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">China</collectingCountry>
(pl. 22, figs 5, 6) with almost circular primary plates, for which the name 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lyman, 1871)" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1871" baseAuthorityName="Lyman" baseAuthorityYear="1871" box="[616,981,904,930]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis box="[616,807,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Ophiura sinensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lyman, T." box="[822,973,904,930]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" pagination="1 - 17" refId="ref16355" refString="Lyman, T. (1871) Supplement to the Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae. Illustrated catalogue of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 6, 1 - 17, pls. 1 - 2. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 40079" type="journal article" year="1871">Lyman, 1871</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
would be available (
<bibRefCitation author="Olbers, J. M. &amp; Griffiths, C. L. &amp; O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Samyn, Y." box="[1216,1425,904,930]" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" refId="ref17400" refString="Olbers, J. M., Griffiths, C. L., O'Hara, T. D. &amp; Samyn, Y. (2019) Field guide to the brittle and basket stars (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) of South Africa. ABCTaxa. Vol. 19. Belgian National Focal Point to the Global Taxonomy Initiative, Brussels, 346 pp." type="book" year="2019">
Olbers 
<emphasis box="[1300,1357,904,930]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). Until the relationships between the putative species have been resolved, we retain the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1866" box="[1181,1375,940,966]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="5" pageNumber="82" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="kinbergi">
<emphasis box="[1181,1375,940,966]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="82">Ophiura kinbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
